Autospa Corp said it has signed anagreement to purchase 2,400,000 shares of eight pct convertiblepreferred stock of Cardis Corp -- representing voting control-- for 15 mln dlrs.    The company said the preferred purchase will be financed byan investment group led by Autospa.    It said it will also receive from Cardis five-year optionsto buy 2,400,000 Cardis common shares at 6.25 to seven dlrseach, depending on the time of exercise, and warrants topurchase about 3,200,000 shares at 6.60 to 7.60 dlrs each.    The company said the exercise of all options and warrantsby Autospa would result in a tital investment of 50 to 55 mlndlrs.  Execution of a definitive agreement is expected by April22, it said, subject to the completion of financingarrangements, and closing is expected by May 15. Reuter&#3;